The incident is believed to have occurred over the weekend after the child was sent to the shop. CAPE TOWN - Police have launched a manhunt for a man who allegedly sexually assaulted an eight-year-old boy in Grabouw. The incident is believed to have occurred over the weekend after the child was sent to the shop. Officers have appealed to the community for assistance in tracking down the perpetrator. The police's Andre Traut said: “The circumstances surrounding the sexual assault which was allegedly perpetrated on 16 September in Grabouw is under investigation. "The suspect is being sought and yet to be arrested.”